[Strangles, a worldwide known highly infectious equine disease entity caused by bacterial infection with _Streptococcus equi_ subspecies _equi_ (referred to as _S. equi_), is not included in OIE's list of notifiable diseases.

For a comprehensive review, please refer to Mod.TG's commentary in posting 20150505.3341538. Typical lesions can be seen at http://www.yourhorse.co.uk/upload/19292/images/Equine%20strangles.jpg. - Mod.AS



A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4133739,281.]
